using UnityEngine;

public class PerformanceError : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Update()
    {
        // Find GameObject every frame
        GameObject player = GameObject.Find("Player");

        // GetComponent every frame
        Rigidbody rb = GetComponent<Rigidbody>();

        // Instantiate every frame
        Instantiate(new GameObject());
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
Finding objects and getting components in Update is expensive.

**The fix:**
```csharp
// Cache references in Start
private GameObject player;
private Rigidbody rb;

void Start()
{
    player = GameObject.Find("Player");
    rb = GetComponent<Rigidbody>();
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Cache references in Start. Don't find or get components every frame."
